  <section id="erm-military-service">
    <h4>Military Service: Rangers and Confederate Records</h4>
    <p>
      Edwin’s wartime service appears across multiple rosters and registers, consistently identifying him as a
      commissioned officer and, in several records, as <strong>Captain</strong>.
      Collectively, these entries show Edwin serving within Ranger-associated Texas units during the Civil War period.
    </p>

    <p>
      Across these records, the recurring pattern is consistent: Edwin is repeatedly identified as a commissioned officer,
      serving in Texas units associated with partisan/ranger organization and later cavalry designations. The resignation notes
      (late 1862) appear more than once and are framed as official and permitted (“leave granted”), suggesting a formal departure.
    </p>
